  "text": "The forced swim test was performed 30 min after the ghrelin treatment in the same manner as our previous report [CITATION_1] . It was carried out in a cylindrical container (11 cm in diameter, 25 cm high) filled with water to the height of 20 cm, and maintained at 25 ± 1°C. After the test, animals were dried with a towel and kept warm before returning them to home cages. Immobility times were manually recorded during the 6 min swim test from captured video of the test. The duration of immobility during the last 4 min of the trial was measured.",
